<lines>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_1">PRIMVM DVBIVM.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_2">V. rerum pretium ex se sit in¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_3">diuisibile, &amp; solum ex no¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_4">stra ignorantia habeat</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_5">latitudinem.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_6">Dvae sunt in re proposita opiniones</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_7">Prima affirmans pretium iustum</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_8">rerum ex se, &amp; ante Deum, qui omnes</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_9">circunstantias videt, &amp; comprehendit</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_10">ex quibus commensuratio rei venditae</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_11">ad pretium taxandum pendet, esse indi¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_12">uisibile: quamuis ex imperfectione co¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_13">gnitionis nostrae, &amp; opinionum vulgi,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_14">&amp; consiliariorum latitudinem habeat.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_15">Ita vt ad pretium illud nec minutissimus</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_16">nummus addi possit, quin pretium iu¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_17">stum excedamus, &amp; sola nos ignorantia</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_18">excusari in pretio latitudinem habente</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_19">constituendo. Vnde aſſerit haec opinio</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_20">si nos reuelationem haberemus omniū</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_21">circunstantiarum ex quibus iusta pretij</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_22">aestimatio pendet: quibus posita reue¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_23">latione pretium iustum necessario, &amp;</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_24">euidenter sciremus, id pretium indiui¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_25">sibile fore futurum: nec tunc latitudinē</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_26">pretii rigorosi mediocris, &amp; pij locum</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_27">habiturem. Sed quia homines sumus</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_28">ignorantiae tenebris oppressi tam reges,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_29">&amp; magistratus taxantes pretia rerum,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_30">quam qui in rempub. pretium cnnsue¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_31">tudine, &amp; vsu inuehunt, quam qui vtro¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_32">que deficiente pretium conuentionale</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_33">sibi constituunt, ideò ignorantia sola,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_34">nos excusari, in pretio latitudinem ha¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_35">bente constituendo, quod in se ipso se¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_36">clusa ignorantia in indiuisibili consistit.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_37">Sicut quando aestimamus Roma, v. g.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_38">vel ipse sol quot ab hinc leucis distet pla</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_39">num est diastantiam illam esse in se, &amp; co</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_40">ram Deo definitam, &amp; indiuisibilem, ta¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_41">men nos quia ignoramus, iusta probabi</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_42">litate in varias opiniones abimus, quod</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_43">in re praesenti magis locum habet, cum</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_44">taxatio pretij, ex quam plurimis circū¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_45">stantijs nobis occultissimis, &amp; collatione</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_46">earum cum alijs, &amp; cum pretio debeat</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_47">pensitari. Ita opinatur Aluarez de con¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_48">tractib.tit. 16. Palacios 2. de contract. cap.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_49">2, Richard. in 1. dist. 33. art. 1. &amp; Gandau.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_50">quodlib. I. q. 40. Probatur, quia iustitia</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_51">consistit inaequalitate, dicente Arist. lib.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_52">1. magn. moral. cap. 34. [quod iuſtum eſt</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_53">aequale eſt] vnde tria inter ſe inaequalia</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_55">cum vno aequalitatem habere non poſ¬</line>
</lines>
